obo:RO_0002333  a  owl:ObjectProperty .

gomodel:SYNGO_4710  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Western blots showed p55 (MPP1) was enriched in synaptic subcellular fractions and enriched in synaptic membranes and PSD fractions (figure 6).\n\n\"r-p55 protein was localized both in soma and dendrites in neuronal cells. Immunocytochemical staining of cultured neurons clearly showed punctate distribution of the protein in neurons. The p55 puncta were partly co-localized with PSD-95, a postsynaptic marker (Fig. 7), and juxtaposed to those of synaptophysin, a presynaptic marker. These results suggested postsynaptic localization of r-p55 protein.\". Experimental description: \"The cerebral cortex of embryonic day 18 or 19 rats (Wistar) was mechanically dissociated and plated onto glass slides coated with polyethylenimine\"\n\n\"We cloned from rat brain a gene that encodes r-p55 protein (GenBankk Accession No. AB098073)\". MPP1/p55 sequence is detailed in Figure 10.\n\nantibody:\n\"anti-human p55 and anti-Homer antibodies were from Santa Cruz Biotechnology Inc. (Santa Cruz, CA)\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-07-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4710" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

